init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You're not sure what the "real job" could be, but you're certain that JFK wouldn't have sent you a letter like this if it

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: you call the number and it rings a few times before a voice answers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: tells you that he needs you to go to Cuba and meet with Castro.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: agree to go to Cuba and meet with Castro.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the public has no idea what you look like.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: met by a man who introduces himself as Castro's personal bodyguard.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You think to yourself "I know that guy from somewhere..." but you can't place him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Cohibas, you get down to business.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You pull the pistol out of your jacket and point it at Castro.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the brown-haired man from the airport, standing there with a smoking gun in his hand.
